 FUSONG, Nov. 16 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Jilin Province, with rich ice and snow resources, has long been one of the most popular skiing destinations in the country. Due to the rising skiing boom around the country in recent years, the ski resorts in Jilin have seized the opportunity to improve their infrastructures and services. As the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics approaches, the general public is expected to continue to unleash their enthusiasm for ice and snow sports.  A skier enjoys the sport at Changbaishan Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Xu Chang)  A skier looks on at Changbaishan Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Xu Chang)  Skiers ride a ski cable car at Changbaishan Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Yan Linyun)  Skiers enjoy the sport at Miaoxiangshan Ski Resort in Changchun, northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhang Nan)  A skier enjoys the sport at Miaoxiangshan Ski Resort in Changchun, northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhang Nan)  Snowmaking machines work at Miaoxiangshan Ski Resort in Changchun, northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhang Nan)  A skier enjoys the sport at Changbaishan Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Yan Linyun)  Skiers pose at Songhuahu Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 14, 2021. (Xinhua)  Skiers ride a ski cable car at Changbaishan Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Xu Chang)  Skiers enjoy the sport at Changbaishan Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Xu Chang)  A skier warms up under the instructions of a coach at Changbaishan Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Xu Chang)  A staff member prepares ski suits at Changbaishan Ski Resort in northeast China's Jilin Province, Nov. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Yan Li